   VA21 OS is built on the shoulders of giants. We are deeply grateful to:

   ### Microsoft AutoGen Project ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
   Special thanks to Microsoft Research and the AutoGen team
   (https://github.com/microsoft/autogen) for their groundbreaking multi-agent
   conversation framework. AutoGen's approach to specialized agents, the AgentTool
   pattern, and reflection capabilities has greatly enhanced VA21's multi-agent
   architecture. The MIT license and Microsoft backing align perfectly with our
   existing Microsoft FARA integration.

   ### Agent Zero Project ü§ñ
   Special thanks to the Agent Zero project (https://github.com/agent0ai/agent-zero)
   for their innovative approach to AI automation. Agent Zero's multi-agent
   framework has inspired our integration of task automation within the VA21
   secure environment. We acknowledge their contribution to the AI automation
   community and thank them for their open-source work.

   ### OpenCode Project üíª
   Special thanks to the SST/OpenCode team (https://github.com/sst/opencode)
   for their excellent multi-agent design with Build and Plan agents, provider-
   agnostic LLM design, and read-only analysis mode. Their MIT-licensed work
   has influenced VA21's role-based agent system.

   ### Debian Project üêß
   This project builds upon the incredible foundation provided by the Debian
   GNU/Linux operating system. We extend our heartfelt gratitude to the Debian
   community for their tireless work in creating and maintaining one of the most
   stable, secure, and versatile operating systems in the world.
   - Website: https://www.debian.org/
   - Debian Social Contract: https://www.debian.org/social_contract

   ### Linux Foundation üêß
   Special thanks to the Linux Foundation for their stewardship of the Linux
   kernel and their work in supporting the open source community that makes
   projects like this possible.
   - Website: https://www.linuxfoundation.org/

